body:
### Describe the bug

Since we are handling all Exceptions with the  `ExceptionMapper<Throwable>` we should never get the default Quarkus error response. 
There is at least one case that an Exception is not handled by our Custom ExceptionMapper.


### Expected behavior

Error response when we call http://localhost:8080/hello should always be:

 "This is custom handler!"

### Actual behavior

Error response when Keycloak server is offline and we call http://localhost:8080/hello with Authorization header in place

```
{
    "details": "Error id b849414c-7207-4533-9cfd-4206733da866-1, io.quarkus.oidc.OIDCException: OIDC server is not available at the 'http://localhost:8001/realms/testing' URL. Please make sure it is correct. Note it has to end with a realm value if you work with Keycloak, for example: 'https://localhost:8180/auth/realms/quarkus'",
    "stack": "io.quarkus.oidc.OIDCException: OIDC server is not available at the 'http://localhost:8001/realms/testing' URL. Please make sure it is correct. Note it has to end with a realm value if you work with Keycloak, for example: 'https://localhost:8180/auth/realms/quarkus'\r\n\tat io.quarkus.oidc.runtime.OidcRecorder.toOidcException(OidcRecorder.java:236)\r\n\tat io.quarkus.oidc.runtime.OidcRecorder$5.apply(OidcRecorder.java:305)\r\n\tat io.quarkus.oidc.runtime.OidcRecorder$5.apply(OidcRecorder.java:299)\r\n\tat io.smallrye.context.impl.wrappers.Slo
```

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11974067/175280101-a8f532a9-8206-420a-90cd-0c67eba2c988.png)


### How to Reproduce?

1. Generate a new Quarkus project:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11974067/175280599-b67faf32-68d0-429f-bd55-f61269720aef.png)

2. Change GreetingResource.java to:
``` java
package org.acme;

import io.quarkus.arc.Priority;

import javax.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;
import javax.ws.rs.GET;
import javax.ws.rs.Path;
import javax.ws.rs.Produces;
import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;
import javax.ws.rs.core.Response;
import javax.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;
import javax.ws.rs.ext.Provider;

@Path("/hello")
public class GreetingResource {

    @GET
    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
    @RolesAllowed("user")
    public String hello() {
        throw new IllegalStateException("Forcing error that handle successfully");
        //return "Hello from RESTEasy Reactive";
    }

    @Provider
    @Priority(Integer.MIN_VALUE)
    public static class AllMissingExceptionsHandler implements ExceptionMapper<Throwable> {

        @Override
        public Response toResponse(Throwable throwable) {
            return Response.status(Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).entity("This is custom handler!").build();
        }
    }

}
```

3. Change application.properties to:
```
quarkus.oidc.client-id=testing-service
quarkus.oidc.auth-server-url=http://localhost:8001/realms/testing
quarkus.keycloak.devservices.enabled=false
```
4. Call http://localhost:8080/hello with postman by providing a new header 
`Authorization:Bearer Just_a_Random_Text` (image)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11974067/175281447-e5c727c2-7c8f-4a9b-bf92-05dda692029a.png)

5. Response is not the expected one (expected:  "This is custom handler!")


